    <summary>Privacy-first static malware analysis tool with MITRE ATT&amp;CK mapping and Teacher Mode.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[## Anya

Anya is a privacy-first static malware analysis tool for Windows, Linux, and macOS.

### Features
- **Multi-format analysis** — PE, ELF, Mach-O, PDF, Office docs, scripts, and more
- **MITRE ATT&CK mapping** — 298 technique explanations with real-world attack examples
- **Teacher Mode** — 39 lessons that explain findings in plain English
- **Privacy-first / fully offline** — zero outbound network calls, ever
- **Risk scoring with verdict** — confidence-calibrated scoring across all file types
- **CLI + GUI** — every feature available in both terminal and desktop app

### What gets installed
- **CLI**: `anya.exe` added to your PATH
- **GUI**: Anya desktop app installed via MSI

### Usage
```
anya --file suspicious.exe
anya --file suspicious.exe --json
anya --file suspicious.exe --explain
anya batch --dir samples/
```

### Links
- [GitHub](https://github.com/elementmerc/anya)
- [Releases](https://github.com/elementmerc/anya/releases)
- [SourceForge](https://sourceforge.net/projects/anya/)
]]></description>
